block.comment: Get the current time in milliseconds. The value returned represents the number of milliseconds since midnight, January 1, 1970 UTC.

Get the current value of a high-resolution time source, in nanoseconds. This value can only be used to measure elapsed time and is not related to any other notion of system or wall-clock time. The value returned represents the number of nanoseconds since some fixed but arbitrary origin time (perhaps in the future, so values may be negative).
